olive oil
1 bag green beans
1 carrot
3 clove garlic
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet dukkah
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
20 g butter
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet Currants
¾ cup water
1 packet couscous
1 bag baby spinach leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar

• Trim and halve green beans. Grate the carrot. Finely chop garlic.
• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken, dukkah, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook half the garlic until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer garlic oil to a small bowl, then add Greek-style yoghurt and stir to combine. Season to taste. Set aside.

• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook green beans and carrot until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• Add remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Add chicken-style stock powder, currants and the water, then bring to the boil. Add couscous and stir to combine.
• Cover with a lid and remove from heat. Set aside until water has absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side.
• Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

• To the saucepan with the couscous, add baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar. Season to taste.
• Divide veggie-loaded currant couscous between plates. Top with dukkah-crusted chicken.
• Dollop with garlic yoghurt to serve. Enjoy!